983
01:41:31,699 --> 01:41:33,409
It's okay if you don't want to talk,
y'know.

984
01:41:33,492 --> 01:41:35,996
I don't wanna talk either, sometimes.

985
01:41:37,873 --> 01:41:39,833
I just like to stay silent.

986
01:41:46,674 --> 01:41:48,093
Do you mind if I sit down?

987
01:41:58,105 --> 01:42:00,734
Do you <i>mind</i> if I sit down?

988
01:42:02,903 --> 01:42:03,945
No.

989
01:42:07,115 --> 01:42:08,076
Thanks.

990
01:42:09,035 --> 01:42:12,331
My legs get a little tired
from standing all the time.

991
01:42:16,461 --> 01:42:18,296
Is this your first visit here?

992
01:42:19,589 --> 01:42:20,507
Yes.

993
01:42:24,179 --> 01:42:27,307
<i>Oh</i> — well, this whole thing must seem
kinda strange to you, huh? 

994
01:42:28,059 --> 01:42:31,145
You realize that I can't see you, even
though you can see me.

995
01:42:32,021 --> 01:42:34,107
Well, that takes a little getting used to.

996
01:42:39,363 --> 01:42:41,366
Am I —
am I looking at your face now?

997
01:42:50,419 --> 01:42:53,087
Oh, god, it don't matter.

998
01:43:07,981 --> 01:43:10,400
If, um — 
if there's anything you wanna talk about —

999
01:43:10,525 --> 01:43:12,777
I'll just listen. 
Alright?

1000
01:43:14,655 --> 01:43:17,324
I'm a <i>real</i> good listener.

1001
01:43:29,465 --> 01:43:31,300
Is there something —

1002
01:43:32,593 --> 01:43:34,846
I dunno —
is there something I can do for ya?

1003
01:43:44,607 --> 01:43:46,859
Do you mind if I take off my sweater?

1004
01:43:49,696 --> 01:43:51,490
I'll just take off my sweater.

1005
01:43:51,740 --> 01:43:53,450
No — <i>no</i> — no.
Don't —

1006
01:43:54,493 --> 01:43:56,662
Please —
please leave it on.

1007
01:44:05,131 --> 01:44:06,216
I'm sorry.

1008
01:44:10,513 --> 01:44:13,516
I just don't know exactly
what it is you want.

1009
01:44:15,560 --> 01:44:17,395
I don't want anything.

1010
01:44:19,773 --> 01:44:23,818
Oh —
why'd you come here, then?

1011
01:44:31,829 --> 01:44:33,664
I wanna talk to you.

1012
01:44:54,939 --> 01:44:56,984
Is there something you wanna tell me?

1013
01:45:00,904 --> 01:45:01,906
No.

1014
01:45:07,288 --> 01:45:10,125
You can tell me —
I can keep a secret.

1015
01:45:21,345 --> 01:45:24,808
Is that all you do —
just talk?

1016
01:45:28,772 --> 01:45:30,523
Well — yeah.

1017
01:45:32,817 --> 01:45:34,277
Yeah — mostly —

1018
01:45:34,944 --> 01:45:36,406
— and listen.

1019
01:45:41,037 --> 01:45:42,581
What else do you do?

1020
01:45:53,802 --> 01:45:55,303
Why are you laughing?

1021
01:45:55,679 --> 01:45:56,889
I'm sorry.

1022
01:46:01,560 --> 01:46:02,604
I'm sorry.

1023
01:46:04,272 --> 01:46:06,441
So what else do you do?

1024
01:46:08,819 --> 01:46:10,613
Nothing, really.

1025
01:46:13,492 --> 01:46:16,412
Oh, well — we're not allowed
to see the customers outta here.

1026
01:46:18,748 --> 01:46:22,878
Yeah? What if you see them —
do you go home with them?

1027
01:46:24,547 --> 01:46:26,215
No sir — we don't.

1028
01:46:29,094 --> 01:46:32,472
We're not allowed to have any outside
relationships with the customers.

1029
01:46:32,764 --> 01:46:35,475
Yeah, but you can really see them
if you want to — can't you —

1030
01:46:35,475 --> 01:46:38,354
I mean, you can go home with them
if you want to — all these places say that.

1031
01:46:38,521 --> 01:46:42,358
I mean — how much extra money do you make?
How much money do you make on the side?

1032
01:46:55,207 --> 01:46:59,251
I'm sorry, sir.
I think you maybe wanna talk to one of the other girls —

1034
01:46:59,296 --> 01:47:01,631
I'll see if I can find one for ya.

1035
01:47:01,631 --> 01:47:03,634
No — no — no — <i>no!</i>

1036
01:47:04,302 --> 01:47:05,845
<i>Please.</i>

1036
01:47:06,000 --> 01:47,07,000
Please.

1037
01:47:08,097 --> 01:47:09,641
Please don't go.

1038
01:47:14,688 --> 01:47:17,650
I just don't think
I'm the one you wanna talk to.

1039
01:47:20,029 --> 01:47:21,405
Please.

1040
01:47:22,824 --> 01:47:24,659
Please don't go — I'm sorry.

1041
01:47:34,378 --> 01:47:35,421
Alright.

1042
01:47:42,721 --> 01:47:45,765
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

1043
01:47:51,566 --> 01:47:52,651
That's okay. 

1044
01:48:02,832 --> 01:48:08,126
Y'know — I know how hard it is
to talk to strangers, sometimes.

1045
01:48:13,675 --> 01:48:15,218
Just relax.

1046
01:48:17,138 --> 01:48:19,265
Relax, and tell me
what's on your mind.

1047
01:48:21,851 --> 01:48:23,228
I'll listen —

1048
01:48:25,773 --> 01:48:26,732
— to you.

1049
01:48:32,406 --> 01:48:34,449
I don't mind listening.

1050
01:48:42,876 --> 01:48:45,087
I do it all the time.

1051
01:49:06,780 --> 01:49:08,282
She was there, wasn't she?

1052
01:49:47,328 --> 01:49:48,704
What's that?

1053
01:49:54,962 --> 01:49:56,129
A vacant lot.

1054
01:49:57,006 --> 01:50:00,716
I bought that land
when we were all together — with your mom.

1056
01:50:04,307 --> 01:50:07,185
I thought we might live there, someday.

1057
01:50:09,521 --> 01:50:10,606
Where?

1058
01:50:11,524 --> 01:50:12,733
Paris —

1059
01:50:13,818 --> 01:50:14,819
Texas.

1060
01:50:15,152 --> 01:50:16,237
Where's that?

1061
01:50:17,906 --> 01:50:19,783
Across the Red River.

1062
01:50:24,956 --> 01:50:26,249
You like it?

1063
01:50:28,168 --> 01:50:29,711
You mean, we'd live on dirt?

1064
01:50:45,272 --> 01:50:48,192
Why do you drink that stuff?
It <i>stinks.</i>

1065
01:50:50,194 --> 01:50:51,654
Wait a minute — where are you going?

1066
01:50:52,071 --> 01:50:53,448
To the truck.

1067
01:51:13,764 --> 01:51:15,098
Have another one?

1068
01:52:24,973 --> 01:52:28,019
This is not a place
to bring a fancy woman.

1069
01:52:30,730 --> 01:52:35,194
Would you say — if you had a fancy woman —
would you bring her in a place like this?

1070
01:52:35,819 --> 01:52:37,696
What's a fancy woman?

1071
01:52:58,055 --> 01:52:59,014
My mother.

1072
01:53:01,808 --> 01:53:03,393
Not <i>your</i> mother —

1073
01:53:04,686 --> 01:53:05,980
but <i>my</i> mother —

1074
01:53:06,648 --> 01:53:08,942
was <i>not</i> a fancy woman.

1075
01:53:09,192 --> 01:53:10,735
She was —

1076
01:53:17,034 --> 01:53:21,290
She never wanted to be a fancy woman —
she never even <i>pretended</i> to be a fancy woman.

1077
01:53:22,291 --> 01:53:23,751
Then what was she?

1078
01:53:24,669 --> 01:53:26,713
She was just — plain.

1079
01:53:29,174 --> 01:53:31,009
Just plain — good.

1080
01:53:32,262 --> 01:53:34,138
She was very good.

1081
01:53:34,764 --> 01:53:35,974
But my daddy —

1082
01:53:38,978 --> 01:53:40,980
See — my daddy had, uh —

1083
01:53:41,939 --> 01:53:43,649
He had this idea —

1084
01:53:43,983 --> 01:53:47,863
he had this idea in his head
that was kind of —

1085
01:53:48,989 --> 01:53:50,699
kind of a sickness —

1086
01:53:52,286 --> 01:53:53,245
What idea?

1087
01:53:54,079 --> 01:53:56,164
He had this idea about <i>her.</i>

1088
01:54:00,044 --> 01:54:01,588
He looked at her —

1089
01:54:03,089 --> 01:54:04,883
but he didn't see her.

1090
01:54:08,220 --> 01:54:09,138
He —

1091
01:54:09,763 --> 01:54:11,599
he saw this idea —

1092
01:54:15,228 --> 01:54:19,609
and he told people that she was from Paris —

1093
01:54:21,652 --> 01:54:23,279
it was a big joke.

1094
01:54:23,613 --> 01:54:25,408
He started telling everybody all the time —

1095
01:54:25,783 --> 01:54:27,869
finally it wasn't a joke anymore —

1096
01:54:31,122 --> 01:54:32,750
He started believing it.

1097
01:54:34,793 --> 01:54:35,920
And —

1098
01:54:36,462 --> 01:54:38,130
He actually believed —

1099
01:54:41,051 --> 01:54:42,260
She —

1100
01:54:43,178 --> 01:54:44,471
Oh, god.

1101
01:54:45,640 --> 01:54:47,767
She would get so embarrassed.

1102
01:54:50,269 --> 01:54:51,312
She'd —

1103
01:54:52,481 --> 01:54:53,941
She was so —

1104
01:54:56,778 --> 01:54:58,738
She was so <i>shy.</i>

1105
01:55:47,796 --> 01:55:49,381
<i>Vamonos, muchacho.</i>

1106
01:56:18,541 --> 01:56:19,752
Left, Dad.

1107
01:56:35,646 --> 01:56:37,522
Hunter — it's me.

1108
01:56:40,652 --> 01:56:45,782
I was afraid I'd never be able to say
the right words to you — in person.


1110
01:56:46,617 --> 01:56:50,371
So — I'm trying to do it like this.

1111
01:56:53,625 --> 01:56:59,005
When I first saw you — this time
at Walt's —

1113
01:57:01,050 --> 01:57:03,886
I was hoping for all kinds of things.

1114
01:57:06,390 --> 01:57:09,602
I was hoping to show you
that I was your father.

1115
01:57:12,230 --> 01:57:14,108
You showed me I was.

1116
01:57:17,861 --> 01:57:20,115
But the biggest thing I hoped for —

1117
01:57:23,034 --> 01:57:24,661
can't come true.

1118
01:57:27,331 --> 01:57:28,916
I know that now.

1119
01:57:31,794 --> 01:57:33,630
You belong together, with your mother.

1120
01:57:36,258 --> 01:57:38,552
<i>You belong together, with your mother.</i>

1121
01:57:40,764 --> 01:57:43,142
<i>It was me that tore you apart.</i>

1122
01:57:43,809 --> 01:57:46,938
<i>And I owe it to you
to bring you back together.</i>

1123
01:57:49,107 --> 01:57:50,984
<i>But I can't stay with you.</i>

1124
01:57:51,443 --> 01:57:53,613
<i>I could never heal up what happened.</i>

1125
01:57:54,822 --> 01:57:57,241
<i>That's just the way it is.</i>

1126
01:57:58,826 --> 01:58:01,622
<i>I can't even hardly remember what happened —</i>

1127
01:58:02,331 --> 01:58:03,749
<i>it's like a gap.</i>

1128
01:58:04,666 --> 01:58:09,339
<i>It left me alone in a way that
I haven't gotten over.</i>

1130
01:58:10,173 --> 01:58:13,133
<i>And right now —
I'm afraid.</i>

1132
01:58:15,305 --> 01:58:18,099
<i>I'm afraid of walking away again.</i>

1133
01:58:18,391 --> 01:58:20,770
<i>I'm afraid of what I might find.</i>

1134
01:58:22,563 --> 01:58:27,607
<i>But I'm even more afraid of
not facing this fear.</i>

1136
01:58:28,570 --> 01:58:30,280
<i>I love you, Hunter.</i>

1137
01:58:32,282 --> 01:58:34,619
<i>I love you more than my life.</i>

1138
01:58:46,091 --> 01:58:47,678
Hey!

1138
01:58:47,091 --> 01:58:48,678
Hey.

1139
01:58:54,601 --> 01:58:56,228
Can I tell you something?

1140
01:58:58,981 --> 01:59:01,359
Sure — anything you like.

1141
01:59:03,152 --> 01:59:04,529
It's kinda long.

1142
01:59:06,281 --> 01:59:07,908
I have plenty of time.

1143
01:59:31,854 --> 01:59:33,480
I knew these people —

1144
01:59:34,274 --> 01:59:35,358
What people?

1145
01:59:37,402 --> 01:59:38,862
These two people —

1146
01:59:44,660 --> 01:59:46,370
they were in love with each other —

1147
01:59:49,708 --> 01:59:51,126
The girl was —

1148
01:59:51,711 --> 01:59:56,050
very young — about 17 or 18 —
I guess.

1149
01:59:57,468 --> 02:00:00,969
And the guy was quite a bit older —

1151
02:00:02,557 --> 02:00:05,352
and he was kinda raggedy and wild —

1152
02:00:06,895 --> 02:00:08,773
and she was very beautiful, y'know?

1153
02:00:11,567 --> 02:00:12,401
Yeah.

1154
02:00:13,194 --> 02:00:17,157
And together, they turned everything
into a kind of an adventure —

1155
02:00:18,617 --> 02:00:20,077
and she liked that.

1156
02:00:21,621 --> 02:00:24,959
Just an ordinary trip
down to the grocery store was —

1157
02:00:25,542 --> 02:00:27,127
full of adventure.

1158
02:00:29,130 --> 02:00:32,008
And they were always laughing
at stupid things.

1159
02:00:32,384 --> 02:00:34,220
He liked to make her laugh.

1160
02:00:35,805 --> 02:00:36,847
And —

1161
02:00:39,058 --> 02:00:41,436
they didn't much care for anything else.

1162
02:00:42,229 --> 02:00:45,649
'Cause all they wanted to do
was be with each other.

1163
02:00:47,568 --> 02:00:49,404
They were always together.

1164
02:00:50,196 --> 02:00:52,407
Sounds like they were very happy.

1165
02:00:54,410 --> 02:00:57,289
Yes. They were — they were real happy.

1166
02:00:58,873 --> 02:00:59,916
And he —

1167
02:01:00,458 --> 02:01:02,169
Hey loved her more than —

1168
02:01:04,588 --> 02:01:06,465
he ever felt possible.

1169
02:01:09,803 --> 02:01:12,180
He couldn't stand being away from her —

1170
02:01:12,264 --> 02:01:14,517
during the day — when he went to work.

1171
02:01:19,731 --> 02:01:21,233
So he quit —

1172
02:01:22,901 --> 02:01:24,653
just to be home with her.

1173
02:01:25,529 --> 02:01:28,074
And then he'd get another job
when the money ran out —

1174
02:01:29,827 --> 02:01:31,662
and then he'd quit again.

1175
02:01:32,330 --> 02:01:35,292
But —
pretty soon, she started to worry.

1176
02:01:39,713 --> 02:01:41,799
'Bout what?

1176
02:01:40,500 --> 2:01:41,799
Money, I guess —

1177
02:01:42,550 --> 02:01:43,926
not having enough —

1178
02:01:44,260 --> 02:01:46,554
not knowing when the next check
was coming in.

1179
02:01:49,016 --> 02:01:51,310
<i>Yep.</i> I know that feeling.

1180
02:01:51,935 --> 02:01:56,438
So — he started to get kinda
torn inside.

1182
02:02:00,278 --> 02:02:01,489
How do you mean?

1183
02:02:02,950 --> 02:02:05,118
Well, he knew he had to work
to support her —

1184
02:02:06,119 --> 02:02:08,539
but he couldn't stand
being away from her, either.

1185
02:02:10,875 --> 02:02:12,168
I see.

1186
02:02:12,710 --> 02:02:15,839
And the more he was away from her,
the crazier he got.

1187
02:02:17,299 --> 02:02:20,052
Except now, he got <i>really</i> crazy.

1188
02:02:23,807 --> 02:02:25,934
He started imagining all kinds of things.

1189
02:02:28,187 --> 02:02:29,146
Like what?

1190
02:02:31,691 --> 02:02:35,195
He started thinking
she was seeing other men on the sly.

1191
02:02:37,198 --> 02:02:42,576
He'd come home from work
and accuse her of spending the day with somebody else.

1193
02:02:42,747 --> 02:02:45,250
He'd yell at her
and break things in the trailer.

1194
02:02:48,379 --> 02:02:49,422
The trailer —

1195
02:02:54,969 --> 02:02:56,054
Yes.

1196
02:02:57,556 --> 02:02:59,391
They lived in a trailer home.

1197
02:03:14,909 --> 02:03:17,747
'Scuse me, sir —
but were you into this with me, the other day?

1198
02:03:19,248 --> 02:03:20,624
I don't mean to pry.

1199
02:03:23,045 --> 02:03:23,920
No.

1200
02:03:25,714 --> 02:03:26,632
Oh.

1201
02:03:30,720 --> 02:03:33,014
I thought I recognized
your voice for a minute.

1202
02:03:34,432 --> 02:03:37,851
No —
wasn't me.

1204
02:03:38,479 --> 02:03:40,563
Mmm-<i>hmm.</i>

1205
02:03:42,777 --> 02:03:43,903
Please go on.

1206
02:03:47,156 --> 02:03:50,452
Anyway — he started to drink real bad —

1207
02:03:51,536 --> 02:03:54,164
and he'd stay out late to test her.

1208
02:03:56,542 --> 02:03:58,378
What do you mean — test her?

1209
02:03:59,462 --> 02:04:01,297
To see if she'd get jealous.

1210
02:04:03,175 --> 02:04:05,260
Heh — mmm-hmm.

1211
02:04:07,721 --> 02:04:11,142
He wanted her to get jealous —
but she didn't.

1212
02:04:11,559 --> 02:04:16,061
She just worried about him —
but that got him even madder.

1214
02:04:17,693 --> 02:04:18,860
<i>Why?</i>

1215
02:04:20,320 --> 02:04:21,863
Because —

1216
02:04:23,116 --> 02:04:25,952
He thought that if she never got jealous of him,
that she didn't really <i>care</i> about him.

1217
02:04:27,787 --> 02:04:31,250
Jealousy was a sign of her love for him.

1218
02:04:32,209 --> 02:04:33,877
And then one night —

1219
02:04:34,920 --> 02:04:38,091
One night, she told him that she was pregnant.

1220
02:04:39,009 --> 02:04:41,594
She was about three or four months pregnant —

1221
02:04:41,970 --> 02:04:43,681
and he didn't even know.

1222
02:04:44,390 --> 02:04:46,601
And then, suddenly, everything changed.

1223
02:04:47,686 --> 02:04:50,773
He stopped drinking
and got a steady job.

1224
02:04:51,649 --> 02:04:53,609
He was <i>convinced</i>
that she loved him now —

1225
02:04:53,693 --> 02:04:55,863
because she was carrying his child.

1226
02:04:56,822 --> 02:05:00,576
And he was going to dedicate himself
to making a home for her.

1227
02:05:01,827 --> 02:05:03,913
But a funny thing started to happen.

1228
02:05:04,456 --> 02:05:05,665
<i>What?</i>

1229
02:05:06,249 --> 02:05:08,543
He didn't even notice it, at first.

1230
02:05:08,918 --> 02:05:10,880
<i>She</i> started to change.

1231
02:05:11,672 --> 02:05:16,215
From the day the baby was born,
she began to get irritated with everything around her.

1233
02:05:16,511 --> 02:05:18,221
She got <i>mad</i> at everything.

1234
02:05:19,474 --> 02:05:22,477
Even the baby seemed
to be an injustice to her.

1235
02:05:23,062 --> 02:05:25,689
He kept trying to make everything
alright for her —

1236
02:05:25,981 --> 02:05:27,441
buy her things —

1237
02:05:27,441 --> 02:05:29,778
take her out to dinner once a week —

1238
02:05:30,487 --> 02:05:32,530
But nothing seemed to satisfy her.

1239
02:05:33,323 --> 02:05:36,786
For two years, he struggled
to pull them back together —

1240
02:05:36,869 --> 02:05:39,246
like the were when they first met.

1241
02:05:40,498 --> 02:05:44,336
But finally, he knew
that it was never gonna work out.

1242
02:05:46,463 --> 02:05:48,256
So he hit the bottle again —

1243
02:05:48,632 --> 02:05:50,843
but this time it got <i>mean.</i>

1244
02:05:51,929 --> 02:05:54,098
This time, when he came home
late at night,

1245
02:05:54,431 --> 02:05:57,143
she wasn't worried about him —
or jealous.

1246
02:05:57,894 --> 02:06:00,063
She was just enraged.

1247
02:06:01,606 --> 02:06:05,943
She accused him of holding her captive
by making her have a baby.

1249
02:06:08,156 --> 02:06:10,451
She told him
that she dreamed about escaping.

1250
02:06:11,160 --> 02:06:13,913
That was all she dreamed about — escape.

1251
02:06:15,123 --> 02:06:18,377
She saw herself at night —
running naked down a highway —

1252
02:06:19,044 --> 02:06:20,921
running across fields —

1253
02:06:21,296 --> 02:06:22,966
running down river beds —

1254
02:06:23,383 --> 02:06:24,635
always running.

1255
02:06:25,094 --> 02:06:29,555
And always, when she was
just about to get away, he would be there —

1257
02:06:29,808 --> 02:06:31,476
he would stop her somehow —

1258
02:06:33,228 --> 02:06:35,147
he would just appear and stop her.

1259
02:06:38,609 --> 02:06:42,238
And when she told him these dreams,
he believed them.

1260
02:06:43,198 --> 02:06:46,616
He knew she had to be stopped,
or she would leave him forever.

1262
02:06:47,327 --> 02:06:52,921
So he tied a cowbell to her ankle,
so he could hear at night if she tried to get out of bed.

1264
02:06:54,044 --> 02:06:57,758
But she learned how to muffle the bell
by stuffing a sock into it.

1265
02:06:58,091 --> 02:07:02,552
And inching her way out of the bed —
and into the night.

1267
02:07:04,223 --> 02:07:06,100
He caught her one night,
when the sock fell out — 

1268
02:07:06,267 --> 02:07:08,603
and he heard her
trying to run to the highway.

1269
02:07:08,770 --> 02:07:14,983
He caught her, dragged her back to the trailer,
and tied her to the stove with his belt.

1271
02:07:16,570 --> 02:07:17,906
He just left her there —

1272
02:07:18,490 --> 02:07:19,949
went back to bed —

1273
02:07:21,409 --> 02:07:23,454
— and laid there, listening to her scream.

1274
02:07:25,164 --> 02:07:27,375
Then he'd listen to his <i>son</i> scream.

1275
02:07:29,585 --> 02:07:34,092
He was surprised at himself,
because he didn't feel anything anymore.

1276
02:07:36,552 --> 02:07:39,264
All he wanted to do was sleep.

1277
02:07:41,558 --> 02:07:45,563
And for the first time, he wished he were far away —

1278
02:07:49,526 --> 02:07:53,197
lost in a deep, vast, country where nobody knew him —

1279
02:07:54,448 --> 02:07:56,158
somewhere without language —

1280
02:07:57,285 --> 02:07:58,620
or streets.

1281
02:08:00,080 --> 02:08:02,875
And he dreamed about this place
without knowing its name.

1282
02:08:04,169 --> 02:08:07,546
And when he woke up,
he was on fire.

1284
02:08:10,427 --> 02:08:13,430
There were blue flames
burning the sheets of his bed.

1285
02:08:14,514 --> 02:08:19,349
He ran through the flames,
toward the only two people he loved —

1287
02:08:20,980 --> 02:08:22,356
but they were gone.

1288
02:08:25,610 --> 02:08:26,945
His arms were burning —

1289
02:08:27,237 --> 02:08:33,156
and he threw himself outside
and rolled on the wet ground —

1291
02:08:36,081 --> 02:08:37,417
Then he ran.

1292
02:08:39,335 --> 02:08:41,421
He never looked back at the fire.

1293
02:08:44,383 --> 02:08:45,718
He just ran.

1294
02:08:52,476 --> 02:08:54,519
He ran until the sun came up —

1295
02:08:56,396 --> 02:08:58,316
and he couldn't run any further.

1296
02:09:00,651 --> 02:09:05,403
And when the sun went down,
he ran again.

1298
02:09:11,123 --> 02:09:13,459
For five days, he ran like this —

1299
02:09:15,628 --> 02:09:17,672
until every sign of man —

1300
02:09:20,717 --> 02:09:22,219
had disappeared.

1301
02:09:33,650 --> 02:09:34,984
<i>Travis.</i>

1302
02:10:18,203 --> 02:10:21,872
If you turn the light off in there,
will you be able to see me?

1304
02:10:29,841 --> 02:10:30,925
I don't know.

1305
02:10:36,307 --> 02:10:37,725
I've never tried.

1306
02:10:56,956 --> 02:10:58,167
Can you see me?

1307
02:11:00,836 --> 02:11:02,129
<i>Yeah.</i>

1308
02:11:03,589 --> 02:11:05,008
Do you recognize me?

1309
02:11:07,969 --> 02:11:09,513
Oh, <i>Travis.</i>

1310
02:11:17,105 --> 02:11:19,149
I brought Hunter with me.

1311
02:11:31,748 --> 02:11:33,083
Don't you want to see him?

1312
02:11:36,253 --> 02:11:37,295
Yeah.

1313
02:11:46,765 --> 02:11:51,061
I wanted to see him so bad,
that I didn't even dare imagine him anymore.

1314
02:11:57,319 --> 02:11:59,823
Ann kept sending me pictures of him —

1315
02:12:03,118 --> 02:12:05,079
until I asked her to stop.

1316
02:12:11,879 --> 02:12:17,697
I couldn't stand the pain of seeing him grow up —
and missing it.

1318
02:12:26,897 --> 02:12:29,524
Why didn't you keep him
with you, Jane?

1319
02:12:32,945 --> 02:12:34,489
I couldn't, Travis.

1320
02:12:39,161 --> 02:12:41,747
I didn't have what I knew he needed.

1321
02:12:48,797 --> 02:12:52,218
I didn't want to use him
to fill all my emptiness.

1322
02:12:57,934 --> 02:12:59,686
Well he needs you now, Jane —

1323
02:13:00,562 --> 02:13:02,022
and he wants to see you.

1324
02:13:02,439 --> 02:13:03,399
He does?

1325
02:13:06,820 --> 02:13:07,737
Yes.

1326
02:13:12,785 --> 02:13:14,995
He's waiting for you.

1327
02:13:15,538 --> 02:13:16,497
Where?

1328
02:13:19,876 --> 02:13:24,044
Downtown — in a hotel —

1330
02:13:26,342 --> 02:13:27,510
The Meridian.

1331
02:13:30,179 --> 02:13:32,182
Room #1520.

1331
02:13:37,179 --> 02:13:39,182
<i>#1520.</i>

1332
02:13:39,984 --> 02:13:41,735
You're not going, are you?

1333
02:13:57,587 --> 02:13:59,423
I can't see you, Jane.

1334
02:14:01,967 --> 02:14:03,386
Don't go yet.

1335
02:14:08,350 --> 02:14:09,685
<i>Don't go yet.</i>

1336
02:14:28,665 --> 02:14:30,125
I —

1337
02:14:32,712 --> 02:14:36,175
I used to make up long speeches
to you, after you left.

1338
02:14:41,389 --> 02:14:45,558
I used to talk to you all the time —
even though I was alone.

1340
02:14:49,816 --> 02:14:52,401
I walked around for months,
talking to you.

1341
02:14:57,407 --> 02:15:00,161
Now — I don't know what to say.

1342
02:15:04,499 --> 02:15:07,378
It was easier when I just imagined you.

1343
02:15:15,513 --> 02:15:18,057
I even imagined you talking back to me.

1344
02:15:23,063 --> 02:15:29,441
We'd have long conversations —
the two of us.

1346
02:15:32,992 --> 02:15:35,578
It was almost like you were there.

1347
02:15:39,958 --> 02:15:43,461
I would hear you —
I would see you — smell you —

1349
02:15:46,048 --> 02:15:47,676
I could hear your voice.

1350
02:15:51,096 --> 02:15:53,391
Sometimes, your voice would wake me up.

1351
02:15:57,020 --> 02:16:00,816
It would wake me up in the middle of the night,
just like you were there in the room with me.

1352
02:16:09,493 --> 02:16:10,452
Then —

1353
02:16:14,166 --> 02:16:16,210
It slowly faded.

1354
02:16:18,338 --> 02:16:20,382
I couldn't picture you anymore.

1355
02:16:24,553 --> 02:16:27,891
I tried to talk out loud to you
like I used to —

1356
02:16:27,891 --> 02:16:29,684
but there was nothing there.

1357
02:16:33,606 --> 02:16:35,525
I couldn't hear you.

1358
02:16:41,323 --> 02:16:42,449
Then —

1359
02:16:48,207 --> 02:16:49,583
I just gave up.

1360
02:16:56,633 --> 02:16:58,260
Everything stopped.

1361
02:17:00,471 --> 02:17:01,514
You —

1362
02:17:06,185 --> 02:17:07,729
just disappeared.

1363
02:17:14,529 --> 02:17:16,489
Now I'm working here.

1364
02:17:22,289 --> 02:17:24,499
I hear your voice all the time.

1365
02:17:30,715 --> 02:17:35,300
Every man —
has your voice.

1367
02:17:54,494 --> 02:17:58,537
I'll tell Hunter that you're coming.

1369
02:18:02,920 --> 02:18:03,630
Travis —

1369
02:18:03,920 --> 02:18:04,630
What?

1370
02:18:09,135 --> 02:18:10,470
I'll be there.

1371
02:18:15,976 --> 02:18:16,852
<i>Good.</i>

1372
02:18:22,776 --> 02:18:26,321
Meridian Hotel —

1372
02:18:24,776 --> 02:18:26,321
Yeah.

1373
02:18:30,160 --> 02:18:34,370
Room #1520.

1375
02:21:23,407 --> 02:21:25,617
Your hair —
it's wet.